    "mental_model": "A clean deal block is a lead with usable facts; due diligence turns it into a decision.",
    "source": "Documents Scanned Most Recent.txt",
    "page": "219",
    "excerpt": "Car Wash Lead - Colonie | 1757 Central Avenue, Colonie, NY | $10M | $1.5M | Est. 0.85 | Scanned location lead from the paperwork. Verify current operator/contact before outreach.",
    "full_text": "ADDENDUM \u2014 Recently Financed / Private Equity T \ncei0ra\u201e,Apa) , Community \nr wash fig Bank\nAbout Hoffman Car Wash \nransactions \nFounded in 1965, Hoffman Car Wash (\"HCW\" or the \"Company\"), led by industry veteran Tom Hoffman Jr., is a \ntop fifty (50) conveyor chain in the US and is located in New York's Capital Region, the Adirondacks, Hudson Valley and \nSouthern Tier. A multi-generational family-run business, HCW has grown to include twenty-two (22) car washes, nine \n(9) Jiffy Lube sites, and an InnovatelT equipment manufacturing company that provides operators with various \ntechnologies and advanced systems such as a reliable chemical dispensing system that consistently helps deliver clean \ncars in both conveyor and self service carwashes; a high-pressure wheel blaster, which is a touchless wheel cleaning \nsystem that automatically adjusts to conveyor speed; and a heavy-duty conveyor that is designed to maximize \nproduction. \nTransaction Overview / History \nIn Jul-20, HCW secured $10MM in financing provided by Community Bank to expand the firm's footprint into central \nNew York and to construct a new headquarters and warehouse in Colonie, NY. The recent financing is part of a string of \ninvestments that Hoffman has made to grow the Company's portfolio to approximately thirty (30) car washes within \nthe next three (3) to five (5) years. InnovatelT Car Wash Equipment's growth mirrors that of the industry, and by late \nsummer, HCW will be moving into a state-of-the-art 25,000-square-foot building, which it will share with the Hoffman \nbusiness' office staff. Interest in the equipment has surged because it is durable and simple to maintain, and as an \nadded benefit of manufacturing its own equipment, Hoffman Car Wash has able to utilize automation to minimize the \nimpact of rising labor costs, which continue to escalate in New York. The new headquarters will house HCW's 20-\nperson office staff, which has outgrown the Company's existing corporate offices located at 1757 Central Avenue in \nColonie, NY. The decision to expand HCW's footprint into central New York will also help to create more opportunities \nfor the firm's employees. More locations will provide managers an opportunity to become district managers, while \ngiving other staff opportunities to undertake new roles and responsibilities. The Company employs about 800 full\u2014 and \npart-time staff. \nBLACKBEAR ASSET MANAGEMENT \n19 \nTHE fv1ORGAN GROUP \nRussell Speeder's",
